description:
&lt;p&gt;This is a fixed term for 12 months. If you are a SBUHB employee you will need to secure your line manager&#39;s permission before applying for this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic and self-motivated support worker with excellent communication and organisational skills to join the Macmillan Advance Care Planning Service in Swansea Bay University Health Board on a 12 month fixed term contract/secondment. The post will be based at Y Rhosyn, Neath Port Talbot Hospital, however applicants should note that there will be a requirement to travel between, and work at other locations across the service, and Swansea Bay University Health Board.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be responsible for co-ordinating the work of the Macmillan Advance Care Planning Service. They will support the work of the Macmillan Advance Care Planning Practitioners and provide a point of contact for patients and professionals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Macmillan Advance Care Planning Support Worker will be a point of contact for the service and will liaise with a variety of service users and professionals on various organisational aspects of the service. The successful applicant will work within a designated team; however will work independently when required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will provide practical support to the smooth running of the sessional commitments in primary and secondary care including individuals, groups and communities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Macmillan Advance Care Planning Support Worker will be responsible for maintaining patient information resources and assisting in the organisation of education programmes for service users, professionals and others.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will provide the administrative support for the Macmillan Advance Care Planning Team, including the ability to use Microsoft Office applications, in particular Excel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Glenda Morris&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Macmillan Advance Care Planning Practitioner&lt;/p&gt;
